<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
You cannot chain-cast the Epic pet, and the GVoc's are inferior in essentially every way to the Epic.  Therefore chain-casting for a magician with the epic is a downgrade...<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I suggest something that I have proposed for a long time. Create a quest NPC that upon being given a Orb of Mastery will return a spell scroll of Manifest Elements.  <br>
<br>
Cast time should be 10 seconds just like any pet spell, this would also have the nice side effect of allowing the Quick Summoning AA to affect our epic.  They actually intended to have this AA work on the epic as one of the patch messages specifically mentioned:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Quick Summoning should now be working on the magician epic<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Finally the recast time could still be set to 5 minutes (however I would wholeheartly support something lower).<br>
<br>
Now, in a line by line examination, lets see what exactly the benefits and drawbacks are:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> BENEFITS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Quick Summoning would now work on the epic pet <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> without any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> coding needed<br>
<br>
No longer have to summon the orb and swap gear twice then destroy the orb (always been a nightmare of mine that I destroy my main hand item doing this)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Impossible</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to multi-quest because the turn in NPC only accepts 1 item, the Orb of Mastery<br>
<br>
Chain-casting would be viable up to 4 epic pets from the 3 currently possible<br>
<br>
(I.E. Orb in inventory,both the Orb and Manifest spell gems ready and 1 existing vs the current situation of 1 existing epic pet, 1 Orb in inventory and spell gem ready)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> DRAWBACKS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Chain-casting would be viable up to 4 epic pets from the 3 currently possible (this one depends on how you view chain-casting...can be good or bad)<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So other than the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> one</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> drawback I mention, which may not be a drawback at all depending on your perspective, this would be a rather painless thing to implement. <p><hr>
